<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>42-1003</num>
  <heading>Special power.</heading>
  <text>A power is special:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(1)</num>
    <text>Where the persons or class of persons to whom the disposition of the lands under the power is to be made is designated;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(2)</num>
    <text>Where the power authorizes the alienation, by means of a conveyance, will, or charge, of a particular estate or interest less than a fee.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1353, ch. 854, § 1039</annotation>
